headline: Kimberly-Clark (NYSE:KMB) Considers US$4 Billion International Tissue Business Sale
summary: Kimberly-Clark (NYSE:KMB) has attracted attention with mergers and acquisition rumors concerning its international tissue business, which drew bids from major players like Royal Golden Eagle and Suzano. This development, part of a broader restructuring strategy, coincides with the company's share price increase of 3% over the last quarter. Despite challenging earnings, including a dip in sales and net income, the bid interest may have supported investor sentiment. Amid broader market gains...

headline: 3 Cash-Producing Stocks in the Doghouse
summary: While strong cash flow is a key indicator of stability, it doesn’t always translate to superior returns. Some cash-heavy businesses struggle with inefficient spending, slowing demand, or weak competitive positioning.
